    "severity": "MEDIUM",
    "category": "spec-compliance",
    "location": "scripts/build/linear_pipeline.py:4564",
    "description": "The new activity_schema gate silently skips an error-correction activity when items is not a list, and also skips any non-mapping entries inside the list. That means malformed writer output such as items: {incorrect: ...} or a scalar list item can produce passed: true with checked: 0, even though it violates the same item-level schema this gate is meant to enforce and will later be ignored or fail in ActivityParser._parse_error_correction. For a schema gate, non-list items and non-mapping item entries should be reported as violations rather than pass-through cases."
  }
